        "content": "<hr class=\"ghq-card-content__horizontal-rule\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"DIVIDER\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">The Invalid C will print in lieu of the barcode on the second FedEx International label when using a ZPL printer in ZPL mode (ZP or ZPL is in the printer name). </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">This is a FedEx bug that we have alerted them to many times. The label prints fine in EPL mode. </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Not all printers print EPL, such as the Zebra 450 printer. So removing the ZP from the name may not always work. </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">ZPL labels are recommended for all label types, because they do look better.  It is not recommended to rename the printer and remove the ZP from the name and print all labels EPL mode going forward. </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">If necessary, it would be better to install a separate driver to the same printer and assign it only to FedEx Express labels. Keep the rest of the labels using ZPL. But remember that not all printers have the ability to print EPL mode, so this fix may not work for every printer. </p>",
