        "content": "<hr class=\"ghq-card-content__horizontal-rule\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"DIVIDER\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">FedEx implemented a change in early 2019 which affects Home Delivery Saturday service. </p><ul start=\"1\" class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST\"><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">FedEx Ground Home Saturday Delivery is available to 1 or 2 day delivery destinations. This means that if you ship on a Thursday or Friday to a 1 or 2 day delivery area, Saturday delivery is still available.&nbsp;</p></li><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">If you ship on Monday, Tuesday, or Wednesday to a 3-5 day delivery area (and the delivery date used to be Saturday) the package will be delivered on the following Monday.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">These changes are reflected in Version 11.7.2. </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\"><span class=\"ghq-card-content__image-container\"><img class=\"ghq-card-content__image\" style=\"width:451px\" src=\"https://api.getguru.com/files/view/b08b13e4-6601-4166-9438-9a3b8c5345f7\" width=\"451\" alt=\"image.png\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"IMAGE\" data-ghq-card-content-image-filename=\"image.png\"></span></p><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">What if Monday is a holiday? </h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">If Monday is a holiday, any Home Delivery shipment would be delivered on Wednesday (rather than Monday or Tuesday). </p>",
