        "content": "<hr class=\"ghq-card-content__horizontal-rule\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"DIVIDER\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Beginning January 27th, 2019, USPS First-Class Package Service (formerly known as Parcel) is zone based, rather than zone \"USA\".   <a href=\"https://www.endicia.com/usps/postage-rate-change/january2019\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"ghq-card-content__link\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"LINK\">https://www.endicia.com/usps/postage-rate-change/january2019</a></p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">This means that a zip code is now required to ship this service and will <mark class=\"ghq-card-content__highlight\" style=\"background-color:#fde892\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"HIGHLIGHT\">no longer</mark> be available on the Quick Postage Screen. To ship FCPS in PostalMate, choose the <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Parcel or document button</strong> and enter a <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Customer</strong> and <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Ship To </strong>and print a 4x6 label for this service. </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\"><span class=\"ghq-card-content__image-container\"><img class=\"ghq-card-content__image\" style=\"width:446px\" src=\"https://api.getguru.com/files/view/cb526c5a-1c60-4bf7-9261-077bc4070928\" width=\"446\" alt=\"image.png\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"IMAGE\" data-ghq-card-content-image-filename=\"image.png\"></span></p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Additionally, Endicia is making a switch to NetStamps postage rolls in Summer of 2019.  This means that Dymo postage labels, or other knock-off brands, will no longer work with Printable Postage.  The NetStamps postage rolls have specific requirements which state: </p><ul start=\"1\" class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST\"><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Valid for use with domestic or international USPS First Class Mail, when mailing letters, postcards and flats or large envelopes\n</p></li><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Note -- NetStamps cannot be used on Packages, Priority Mail or Priority Mail Express due to USPS regulations\n</p></li></ul><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">\nThese additional requirements specified by USPS does mean that First Class Package Service will <mark class=\"ghq-card-content__highlight\" style=\"background-color:#fde892\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"HIGHLIGHT\">not</mark> be an option on the Quick Postage screen, as you will not be allowed to use NetStamps on packages.  It may also mean that the ability to print stamps for Priority Mail or Media Mail mail may also be removed later this year. </p>",
