        "content": "<p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Here is a detailed description about the problem: \n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">1.- We can enable/disable a carrier for a store in 4 different ways\n</p><ul start=\"1\" class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST\"><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">needs to check carrier settings in storegroup level and store level</p></li></ul><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">-As a setting at StoreGroup level\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">-As a setting at Store level\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">-As a record in table CarrierByStoreGroup(trough Carrier Settings in portal)\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">-As a record in table CarrierByStore (trough Carrier Settings in portal)\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">and we use differents ways to obtain if the carrier is active or not this is the main problem. We need to improve some store procedures and tables to handle this.\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Currently at store group level Benavides in QA has been  activated Canda Post and UPS that's why those carriers are showed in that modal.\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">\n</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">2.- The table DataPull where we are getting last date when a setting was updated in portal is not taking consideration of the tables CarrierByStore and CarrierByStoreGroup so that's why we have to delete our local settings then disable those carriers and activate again our store.</p>",
        "owner": {
