        "content": "<hr class=\"ghq-card-content__horizontal-rule\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"DIVIDER\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Default values for Invoice term and email values are set here.</p><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">Maximum Term</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Select from the drop down list what the maximum NET term you wish to offer for invoice accounts.&nbsp;</p><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">Late Fees</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">You have the option to asses late fees for all invoice accounts prior to running statements. This option is found in CashMate under <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Tools </strong>&gt; <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Invoice Mass Late Fees</strong>.</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Enter a late fee dollar amount and/or late fee percentage, as well as the late fee days (how many days late (past the due date) for late fees to apply. The late fee is assessed per late invoice (based on late fee days) and the higher amount of the $ or % amount prevails. Late fees can be reversed on the individual account as needed.</p><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">Email</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Check the box if you wish to send invoices and invoice statements via email.</p><ul start=\"1\" class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST\"><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\"><strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Invoice email</strong>: Type in the text you wish to display in the body of the email for invoices.</p></li><li class=\"ghq-card-content__bulleted-list-item\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BULLETED_LIST_ITEM\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\"><strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Invoice statements</strong>: Type in the text you wish to display in the body of statements for invoicing.</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">How to get to Invoice Settings</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">In CashMate, choose <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Tools </strong>&gt; <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Options </strong>&gt; <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Account Receivable Settings </strong>and click on the Invoices tab.</p>",
