    {
        "content": "<hr class=\"ghq-card-content__horizontal-rule\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"DIVIDER\"><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">Time Clock Enabled</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">The Time Clock can be enabled or disabled from the <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Tools</strong> menu on any station.</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Check the box \"Time clock enabled on this station\".&nbsp;</p><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">Log-on Options</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Fingerprint Reader: &nbsp;This is a secure method of clocking in and out. Fingerprint readers can be setup on one or all stations in a network. &nbsp;</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Name: If fingerprint reader is not selected, \"Name\" will be defaulted. Choose \"Password required\" to help secure log-ons with a password. (Each Time Clock user must be set up with a password). &nbsp;If using a fingerprint reader, also checkmark Password required to enforce security with a password when a fingerprint reader is not present.</p><h2 class=\"ghq-card-content__medium-heading\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"MEDIUM_HEADING\">How to get to Time Clock Settings</h2><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">From System Utilities, choose <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Tools </strong>&gt; <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Settings </strong>&gt; <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">Time Clock</strong></p>",
