        "content": "<hr class=\"ghq-card-content__horizontal-rule\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"DIVIDER\"><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Cayan sent the following email to some customers on January 24, 2019.  We have confirmed that it is a legitimate email, and the store needs to call Cayan to update their processor, which may require a change on their terminal.  The POS software (CashMate) is not an issue. </p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Dear Valued Merchant:<br><br>As part of our ongoing efforts to transition our services to TSYS, you will need to make an important update to your point-of-sale software payment processing information. This update will require you to contact your point of sale vendor to make the necessary changes to your system.<br><br><strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">It is imperative that you call us immediately</strong> at the provided number below. Our representatives will provide you with the information required to give to your vendor to successfully complete this process.<br><br>Unless we hear from you, beginning on February 8, we will be placing your account in a suspended state <strong class=\"ghq-card-content__bold\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"BOLD\">and you will be unable to complete a transaction</strong>. If we do not hear from you by February 23, this shall serve as notice of termination of your merchant transaction processing agreement with an effective date of February 24.<br><br>Please call a representative at <a href=\"https://url.emailprotection.link/?aTefksrqXgx89KdlLPDJGqk3no6iGFYQ4CWJ_hIAgEncetirF6zsfv8AdqfPC-Mb4pi7_bRiBIMTbZ_fOnFSUBA~~\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"ghq-card-content__link\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"LINK\">855-276-6401</a> between 9 a.m. and 5 p.m. EST, Monday-Friday as soon as possible.</p><p class=\"ghq-card-content__paragraph\" data-ghq-card-content-type=\"paragraph\">Sincerely,<br>The Cayan Support Team</p>",
